# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code when working with code in this repository.

## Read this first when starting a session

**Cross-project durable rules.** This project carries a local copy of Marc's [claude-rules](https://github.com/marc-leonti/claude-rules) in the [`claude_rules/`](claude_rules/) directory. Two files are required reading at the start of every session:

- [`claude_rules/claude_user_rules.md`](claude_rules/claude_user_rules.md) — the short durable behavioral rules (the Hat Rule, hedging language, treating pushback as data, etc.).
- [`claude_rules/lessons_learned.md`](claude_rules/lessons_learned.md) — the cross-project narrative wisdom log. Read before starting any deep investigation.

Those rules apply across all of Marc's projects and are committed locally to this repo because the iOS Claude Code sandbox does not persist `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` between sessions. Treat them as load-bearing. They layer on top of the project-specific rules in this file.

If you want the longer reference form (distilled principles + onboarding for newcomers), also read [`claude_rules/getting_started_with_claude.md`](claude_rules/getting_started_with_claude.md).

**If a new lesson is earned during this session**, edit `claude_rules/lessons_learned.md` (or whichever rules file the lesson belongs in). The change stays in this project until Marc syncs it to the canonical [marc-leonti/claude-rules](https://github.com/marc-leonti/claude-rules) repo on his desktop. To check sync status at any time:
```
python3 claude_rules/claude_rules_sync.py
```

If `claude_rules/` is missing from this project (fresh clone, or an older project that hasn't been bootstrapped), run:
```
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/marc-leonti/claude-rules/main/bootstrap.sh | bash
```

